Irrigation is the artificial supply of water to crops at regular intervals to support growth by replenishing soil moisture. Two methods that conserve water are: 
1. Drip Irrigation – where water is delivered drop by drop near the plant roots, minimizing water loss by evaporation and runoff; 
2. Sprinkler Irrigation – where water is sprayed through pipes with rotating nozzles, ensuring even distribution and reduced wastage on uneven terrain.
